BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:cmc-dmarc-sonic-arts-residency-2026-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260713T115347Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260805
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260806
SUMMARY:Deadline: CMC/DMARC Sonic Arts Residency 2026/2027
DESCRIPTION:The Digital Media and Arts Research Centre (DMARC) and CMC Irel
 and announce the second year of the Sonic Arts Residency Programme at the 
 University of Limerick Electronic Music Studio for 2026/27. The residency 
 offers Irish and international composers and sound artists an opportunity 
 to develop their creative practice and experiment using UL's facilities. F
 ACILITIES: the Electronic Music Studio (EMS) featuring both digital and an
 alogue workflows\, including a bespoke Buchla 200e\; a 32-channel immersiv
 e sound lab (SpADE)\; a makerspace supporting electronics and fabrication\
 ; and a range of well-equipped recording studios with a wide selection of 
 microphones and production hardware and software. DMARC is based in the Co
 mputer Science and Information Systems Department at UL and has a long his
 tory supporting digital arts\, electronic music\, and computer-aided compo
 sition (hosting the 2022 International Computer Music Conference and 2020 
 International Conference on Live Coding\, the Diffusion Prize with RTE Lyr
 ic FM\, and partnering with Light Moves Festival). PROGRAMME: each residen
 cy lasts 10 working days within one of two windows\, September-December 20
 26 or January-March 2027. Support includes a EUR 1\,000 honorarium from CM
 C\, a travel bursary up to EUR 350\, and an accommodation bursary up to EU
 R 1\,400 (ten nights)\, with DMARC helping identify accommodation. There i
 s an outreach/presentation element: a one-hour talk/performance for the DM
 ARC community of students and researchers\, and required documentation of 
 the process (photo\, video\, recordings\, and/or written reflections) that
  may be published by CMC on social media\; artists may also be invited to 
 contribute to CMC's amplify podcast series or online features at cmc.ie/fe
 atures. The programme runs 2025-27 with support for six artists (4 Irish\,
  2 international). ASSESSMENT: candidates apply via an online form submitt
 ing a CV\, work samples\, an outline of the residency project (including t
 echnical requirements)\, how they propose to engage with the facilities\, 
 and how the residency would benefit their practice. Criteria: artistic qua
 lity of the proposal including development of work using either the SpADE 
 system or Buchla 200e\; how the opportunity supports the candidate's curre
 nt career stage and artistic goals\; demonstrated technical capacity to en
 gage with the facilities\; and balanced representation of genres\, gender\
 , and geographical regions. TO APPLY: complete the online application form
  linked from the opportunity page. Closing date: 11am (IST)\, 5 August 202
 6\; late applications will not be accepted. Questions: jurgen.simpson@ul.i
 e or kfennell@cmc.ie. Applications are jointly assessed by DMARC and the C
 ontemporary Music Centre.\n\nOrganisation: Contemporary Music Centre (CMC)
  & Digital Media and Arts Research Centre (DMARC)\, University of Limerick
 \nLocation: University of Limerick\, Limerick\, Ireland (in person).\nAwar
 d: EUR 1\,000 honorarium (from CMC)\, plus a travel bursary up to EUR 350 
 and an accommodation bursary up to EUR 1\,400 (ten nights). No application
  fee.\nDuration: 10 working days\, scheduled within one of two windows: Se
 ptember-December 2026 or January-March 2027. Additional time may be reques
 ted where it does not incur extra cost.\n\nMore: http://cmc.ie/opportuniti
 es/open-call-cmcdmarc-sonic-arts-residency-20262027?utm_source=artificialn
 ouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:http://cmc.ie/opportunities/open-call-cmcdmarc-sonic-arts-residency-202
 62027?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:University of Limerick\, Limerick\, Ireland (in person).
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:atheras-nicosia-ludic-lab-toyful-music-festival-2026@artificialnouveau.
 github.io
DTSTAMP:20260713T115347Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260715
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260716
SUMMARY:Deadline: Atheras: Nicosia Ludic Lab for Composers\, Toyful Music F
 estival 2026
DESCRIPTION:Atheras Peoples and Cultures invites composers and performer-re
 searchers to apply for the Nicosia Ludic Lab\, a 31-day international resi
 dency dedicated to exploring 'play' as a compositional and performative me
 thodology in contemporary music. Building on the artistic vision of the To
 yful Music Festival\, the residency creates a focused environment where ex
 perimentation\, precision\, and imagination coexist\, redefining how music
  is conceived\, structured\, and performed. The residency runs in Nicosia\
 , Cyprus\, from 23 October to 22 November 2026\, and participants develop 
 new ensemble works that directly shape the artistic programme of the Toyfu
 l Music Festival 2026. ELIGIBILITY: applications are open to individual ar
 tists (proposals from duets or collectives will not be considered) based i
 n a Creative Europe country\, who must demonstrate a strong interest in ex
 perimental\, ensemble-based practices. SELECTED RESIDENTS RECEIVE: full fi
 nancial support (travel\, accommodation\, daily allowance)\; shared accomm
 odation in central Nicosia\; continuous access to a professional ensemble\
 ; mentorship sessions and individual meetings with ensemble members\; coac
 hing sessions with composer and conductor Andys Skordis\; artistic and pro
 fessional guidance from the Atheras team\; rehearsal space and full produc
 tion support for Phase 3\; and video and audio recording of the final live
  concert for documentation and international visibility. Deadline: 15 July
  2026.\n\nOrganisation: Atheras Peoples and Cultures\nLocation: Nicosia\, 
 Cyprus\; open to individual artists based in a Creative Europe country\nAw
 ard: Full financial support: travel\, shared accommodation in central Nico
 sia\, and daily allowance. Rehearsal space and full production support pro
 vided\; final live concert recorded (video and audio) for documentation an
 d international visibility.\nDuration: 31-day residency\, 23 October to 22
  November 2026\n\nMore: https://on-the-move.org/news/atheras-nicosia-ludic
 -lab-composers-new-works-toyful-music-festival-2026-cyprus?utm_source=arti
 ficialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://on-the-move.org/news/atheras-nicosia-ludic-lab-composers-new-wo
 rks-toyful-music-festival-2026-cyprus?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdes
 k&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Nicosia\, Cyprus\; open to individual artists based in a Creative 
 Europe country
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:vfa-sonic-connections-open-call-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260713T115347Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260719
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260720
SUMMARY:Deadline: Sonic Connections Open Call 2027 (Villa Filanda Antonini)
DESCRIPTION:Villa Filanda Antonini (VFA) launches its Spring Open Call to s
 elect up to 4 artists and professionals for a one-month residency in March
  2027 on the theme 'Sonic Connections'\, focused on experimental music\, s
 ound art\, and performances. Hosted at Villa Filanda Antonini\, a former s
 ilk mill in Villorba\, Italy\, the project brings together four internatio
 nal artists and professionals to examine the relationship between architec
 ture\, landscape\, and collective sonic experience. ADDRESSED TO: artists\
 , performers\, curators\, designers\, and professionals not currently resi
 ding in Italy. GRANT & BENEFITS: a fully funded residency covering mentori
 ng\, accommodation\, travel costs\, production costs\, and a daily salary\
 , plus a EUR 1\,000 residency stipend. WHEN: 1-31 March 2027. HOW TO APPLY
 : complete the application form and attach a CV\, portfolio\, project prop
 osal\, and letter of reference. The VFA residency program has been selecte
 d under conditions by Culture Moves Europe\, a project funded by the Europ
 ean Union and implemented by the Goethe-Institut. Deadline: 19 July 2026\,
  23:59 CEST.\n\nOrganisation: Villa Filanda Antonini (VFA)\nLocation: Vill
 orba\, Italy (a former silk mill). Addressed to artists and professionals 
 NOT currently residing in Italy.\nAward: Fully funded residency covering m
 entoring\, accommodation\, travel costs\, production costs\, and a daily s
 alary\, plus a EUR 1\,000 residency stipend.\nDuration: One-month residenc
 y\, 1-31 March 2027.\n\nMore: https://www.vfa.art/events/sonic-connections
 -open-call-2027/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.vfa.art/events/sonic-connections-open-call-2027/?utm_source
 =artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Villorba\, Italy (a former silk mill). Addressed to artists and pr
 ofessionals NOT currently residing in Italy.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:musikfonds-stip-6-ai-scholarship-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260713T115347Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260630
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260701
SUMMARY:Deadline: Musikfonds: STIP-6 AI Scholarship Programme 2027 (Germany
 )
DESCRIPTION:STIP-6 is a Musikfonds scholarship programme supporting profess
 ional musicians who work on AI-based composition and who reflect criticall
 y and societally on the role of artificial intelligence in music. Ten scho
 larships of EUR 30\,000 each are awarded for the 2027 working year. Open t
 o Germany-based professional freelance musicians across genres\; no comput
 er-science or technical background is required. Deadline 30 June 2026\, 18
 :00 CET. Details and application via the Musikfonds funding programmes pag
 e (apply at musikfonds-antrag.de). NOTE: this entry was sourced from resea
 rch and the funder's pages may update\; confirm current figures and deadli
 ne before applying.\n\nOrganisation: musikfonds e.V.\nLocation: Germany. O
 pen to Germany-based professional freelance musicians\; no computer-scienc
 e background required.\nAward: EUR 30\,000 lump sum per scholarship\, paid
  in twelve monthly installments across January to December 2027. Ten schol
 arships available. No application fee.\nDuration: Twelve months (January t
 o December 2027).\n\nMore: https://www.musikfonds.de/foerderprogramme?utm_
 source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.musikfonds.de/foerderprogramme?utm_source=artificialnouveau
 grantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Germany. Open to Germany-based professional freelance musicians\; 
 no computer-science background required.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:musikfonds-small-project-funding-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260713T115347Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260831
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260901
SUMMARY:Deadline: Musikfonds: Small Project Funding (New and Experimental M
 usic) 2026 (Germany)
DESCRIPTION:Musikfonds Small Project Funding supports new\, experimental an
 d contemporary music projects with grants of up to EUR 3\,000\, prioritisi
 ng projects in rural and structurally weaker regions of Germany. A minimum
  10 percent co-financing is required and the artist fee must be at least E
 UR 350 per concert. Applicants and projects must be based in Germany. Appl
 ication windows close 31 August 2026 and 30 November 2026. NOTE: research-
 sourced\; confirm current figures and window dates on the Musikfonds site 
 before applying.\n\nOrganisation: musikfonds e.V.\nLocation: Germany. Appl
 icants and projects based in Germany\; priority to rural and structurally 
 weaker regions.\nAward: Up to EUR 3\,000 per project (minimum 10 percent c
 o-financing\; artist fee at least EUR 350 per concert). No application fee
 .\nDuration: Project-based.\n\nMore: https://www.musikfonds.de/foerderprog
 ramme?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.musikfonds.de/foerderprogramme?utm_source=artificialnouveau
 grantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Germany. Applicants and projects based in Germany\; priority to ru
 ral and structurally weaker regions.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
